From: Thomas Renninger <trenn@suse.de>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 11:24:38 +0200
Subject: Revert "ACPICA: Replace strncpy() with strscpy_pad() in
 acpi_ut_safe_strncpy()"
References: bsc#1268472
Git-repo: https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/rafael/linux-pm.git
Git-commit: bf128cd8674f82b60feea66809874064855db2b0
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository

Revert commit 97f7d3f9c9ac ("ACPICA: Replace strncpy() with
strscpy_pad() in acpi_ut_safe_strncpy()") because it broke compilation
of ACPI utilities [1] even though it was not expected to make any
functional difference.

Closes: https://lore.kernel.org/all/79e9e913-0fb1-4110-804b-c3b5d0edafe4@kernel.org [1]
Reported-and-tested-by: Jiri Slaby <jirislaby@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Thomas Renninger <trenn@suse.com>
Cc: 7.1+ <stable@vger.kernel.org> # 7.1+
[ rjw: New changelog ]
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260617092448.538721-1-trenn@suse.de
Signed-off-by: Rafael J. Wysocki <rafael.j.wysocki@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/acpi/acpica/utnonansi.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/acpi/acpica/utnonansi.c
+++ b/drivers/acpi/acpica/utnonansi.c
@@ -168,7 +168,8 @@ void acpi_ut_safe_strncpy(char *dest, ch
 {
 	/* Always terminate destination string */
 
-	strscpy_pad(dest, source, dest_size);
+	strncpy(dest, source, dest_size);
+	dest[dest_size - 1] = 0;
 }
 
 #endif
